{"key":"processedPost-12436921","value":{"id":12436921,"first":12435104,"last":12934711,"when":1271953144,"utime":"04/22/10 07:19 PM","content":"A four hour or greater soak is fine, but don't go over 24.&nbsp; Disregard bad advice above not to boil.&nbsp; I bring grains to a <b>rapid boil</b> for ten minutes.&nbsp; It's important to start the grains in cold water and then bring to a boil.&nbsp;  NEVER bring water to a boil and dump your grains in.&nbsp; That will lead to burst kernels and release of starch.&nbsp; <br />RR","title":"Re: Preparing rye","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}